The paper discusses the use of distributed intelligence mechanisms, such as Neural Networks and Support Vector Machines, to optimize the operation of a Digital Ecosystem. This involves learning-based pattern recognition functionality and evolutionary and ecological dynamics, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
